        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 7 at 4:52PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 451 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Swancreek, or over Jonesville, moving northeast at
45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Elkin...
Fairview...
Jonesville...
Boonville...
East Bend...
Ronda...
and Nebo.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
